<section xml:id="sec-Integers" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Integers</title>
    <introduction>
         <p>
            <term>Integers</term> are a fundamental concept in mathematics with wide applications
            in real-life situations. In sports and games, points, scores, and 
            rankings are often represented using integers. In Grade <m>7</m>, 
            you learned about whole numbers. In this section, we will take 
            a step further to explore <term>integers</term>. 
         </p>
    </introduction>
    <objectives>
        <introduction>
            <p>
                By the end of this substrand, you should be able to:
            </p>
        </introduction>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Represent <alert>integers</alert> on a number line.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Use a number line to perform <alert>addition</alert> and <alert>subtraction</alert> of integers.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Solve expressions involving <alert>combined operations</alert> of integers using a number line.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </objectives>
    
